name: Shea Gerrian
text:
We've ordered from this location many times and have always had an amazing experience.
Tonight we were able to use a 40% off an order from our email (completely worth …More

name: Kimberly Inmon
text: Pizza cheaper than their delivery counterparts and 100 times more delicious. I always call ahead, never a wait. You really can't beat just baked pizza at home.

name: jim wilson
text: Papa Murphy pizza is the best!  Friendly staff, quick service, design your own pie. Love at 425°. Love baking at home.

name: Sheila Johnson
text: Very nice employees. The pizza was super good, the Mediterranean Fab.

name: shannah stockstill
text: Great take and bake pizzas. Always fresh and quite a variety of toppings to choose from.

name: Diamond Grit
text: Best quality by far.  Plus you can pick it up and keep it in your freezer or fridge to cook at a later date.  It has the best cheese!

name: Pamela Cook
text: The pizza choices are very good. I like that you bring your pizza home to cook cause I have control over how the crust comes out.

name: tim teague
text: Great food, killer prices, the store is always neat and clean and the staff is very friendly.  This is a once a week stop for us and we'll keep coming back.

name: Evalena Chaffin
text: Love this place! Great pizzas with plentiful toppings!

name: Stray Driver
text: Always fresh. Staff is amazing. Great deals too. Check em out

name: Jod B
text: Just a thank you review to say that this location is perminantly closed.

name: John Castillo
text: Service is prompt,  food is easy to pick out or up.

name: Ben Fischer
text: Really friendly and fast work for a walk-in

name: Chance Cuthbertson
text: Friendly and helpful, pizza was excellent

name: Sibel Nadir
text: This is just preference of taste. I prefer ordered pizza but that doesn't mean others wouldn't like the multitude of ways you can build your pizza at papa Murphy's

name: Felix Coronado
text: Love the pizza here so good and fresh

name: Josh Hollinger
text: If you have never ordered a pizza place from this place before, you order the pizza how you want it...then you pick it up, and cook it at home yourself.  They do not cook the pizza for you.  Kinda sucks if your looking for something ready to eat, but the pizza is pretty good.

name: Steven Guenther
text: Awesome pizza, great service, I can afford it once a week!

name: Adam Watters
text: The chain is great. This location needs twice as many employees. Very understaffed.

text: Great pizza and prices

text: A great alternative to the traditional pizza shops. Kids love it!
